$PAR
What is the force per meter on a lightning bolt at the equator that carries \($current \, \(\textrm{A}\) perpendicular to the Earth's \($strength\) \(\times 10^{-5} \, \(\textrm{T}\) field?
$PAR

\{ans_rule(40)\} \(\textrm{N/m}\)

$PAR
END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp("$E"));

BEGIN_HINT
